# Codex Adversarial Review

Target: branch diff against e0617347786e9ece74a09d5a6459a3dbaea94dd1
Verdict: needs-attention

No-ship: the change can either commit pipeline state or run an autonomous fixer without a valid adversarial-review finding set.

Findings:
- [high] Missing fallback sentinel triggers automated edits instead of a hard stop (scripts/execute-pipeline.sh:820-843)
  The UNKNOWN branch says it is escalating to manual review, but it actually sets `_has_findings=true`, which immediately enters the Codex fix loop and grants Edit/Write/Bash against whatever is in `CODEX_FILE`. If Claude omits the sentinel, or if the adversarial review failed and the output was replaced with an unavailable/no-findings message, the fixer has no concrete findings to resolve and the pipeline can still proceed after build passes. That is not a manual-review escalation; it risks hallucinated changes or shipping without a successful adversarial review.
  Recommendation: Treat UNKNOWN and adversarial-review failure as blocking: end the stage and exit non-zero, or require a structured findings block before invoking the fixer. Do not run the fix session on missing-sentinel output.
- [medium] Lenient clean-tree check can allow pipeline state into commits (scripts/check-clean-tree.sh:71-91)
  The default clean-tree check only warns when `.iago/state/` is not ignored, then filters all untracked `.iago/state/` entries and returns CLEAN. Inference from the pipeline code: later staging excludes secrets only, not `.iago/state/**`, so a repo without the intended ignore rule can pass pre-flight and then have lock/run NDJSON artifacts staged by `git add -A` or the PR session.
  Recommendation: If `.iago/state/` is not covered by ignore rules, fail the clean-tree check instead of warning, or add `.iago/state/**` to every staging exclusion path. Add a test with no `.gitignore` coverage and an untracked `.iago/state` file.

Next steps:
- Block the PR until UNKNOWN adversarial verdicts stop the pipeline or require human review.
- Tighten `.iago/state` handling so generated pipeline state cannot be committed accidentally.
